description:
For 400 years the Israelites have cried out for God to save them from Egyptian brutality. Now, after generations of persecution, God is beginning to stand in the heavens. The Tenth is about two Israelite slaves, Adinah and Nu, and their new baby boy. Reeling from unbelievable hardship, they begin to make efforts to find a spotless lamb all before the tenth plague arrives. Nu, still placing strong faith in God, forges forward in hope and belief that God can and will provide, while Adinah battles depression and anger as memories of her late father torment her confidence that God cares for her. Time is withering. The door must be painted with the blood of a perfect lamb. The Tenth plague is coming. 

Directed By: The Cook Brothers
Starring: Sara Al-Bazali, Roman Maldonado, Tyler Jones-Palmer, Alessandra Leone
